Local joint that's somehow kept itself a heavyweight contender in the DC pie game for decades.  Despite the transient coming and going of pizza chains which catered to the demand brought on by the "neapolitan renaissance " that furiously saturated the DC restaurant, Pizzoli's has remained independent in one location for over 20 years.  Most closely comparable to Famous Luigi's, Pizzoli's has remained who they've been true to themselves and what they offer....consistent quality, classic style (I guess called NY style if you need some frame of reference) with eclectic options to choose.  Unfortunately Luigi's had to close it's doors in 2013, but still remains a legend with hard shoes to fill along with other local staples who's shoes no one will ever fit into again (Armand's Chicago Pizzeria).  Fortunately Pizzoli's had made it this far and I hope it doesn't suffer a similar fate but very likely for the reason it's so good.  It's definitely an establishment that isn't interested in corporate backing, looking to accommodate to trends or pander to budget friendly gimmicks.  Which might click with a handful of you readers out there, but they're like Four Seasons insofar as their quality is the cornerstone of how they treat each customer and pizza pie...equally great pizza, that's it, no rewards, no games, but most importantly, no doubt if you like it or not.  Pizza preferences are always highly subjective, Pizzoli's Pizzeria is worth challenging your palate.

Lots of other choices if you don't want pizza.  Staff is friendly.  By the way, a "slice" is really 1/4 of a large pizza.  Garlic bread is really garlic-y (a good thing)!
Super friendly staff, awesome pizza at very good price. Would recommend to everyone!
There jumbo slices are like that.they get five stars from me.they are very friendly and respectful.its very clean in there also.and they sell ice cream.
Ok, so not my favorite pizza place, but it's open late and has the benefit of being the only food around. Slices are absolutely gigantic. I promise, you only need one.
This place has really excellent pizza. Taste more Italian then most pizza in D.C. little pricey but well worth it.

Pizzoli's is definitely my favorite pizzeria in DC!  They offer a great variety of custom pizzas and savory sauces.  We always order our pizzas "lightly baked" in order to really appreciate the delicious crust.  We also use Pizzoli's for catering at my office.  They are consistently prompt when we order for delivery.  I highly recommend them to one and all!
Awesome 🍕...
Best Pizza I’ve had in a long time. And I’m a food critic. It’s simple but delicious. All the flavored blended together excellently.
Tasteless pre made frozen meatball parmesan sub large bottle drink $15 some change and you'd expect tips on top of that expensive not worth it could've bought nice entree somewhere decent
Great food & fast delivery! They have a solid gluten-free menu as well.

I happened upon this "mom & pop" place while out walking near my hotel and I'm glad I did. They have several specialty pizzas available and the staff was pretty friendly. I got one of their Hawaiian specialty pizzas and it was phenomenal! They are generous with their toppings and by the flavor I could tell they were all fresh. Great value for the price!
The stromboli is awesome!
Solid, huge slices. Nice sauce. 3.5 ⭐
Great eggplant and artichoke pizza! Hard working staff as well.
I love Pizzolis, Chicken cheese steak, and Pizza! Yummy!!
nice pizza and great staff. Plus, the fact it is open so late is really wonderful.
Hands down best chicken basil pizza I've ever had!  Great fresh ingredients...amazing crust...can't say enough good things about this place!
I ordered crispy buffalo wings here and sweet potato chips. They didn't disappoint with the food and the service was good. Quite a hidden lil place without google though
good pizza. convenient location. and open late

Delicious pizza! All natural ingredients which is why the price is a little higher. Definitely worth a visit!
It was pretty bad. Came at 11pm and got some old gross pizza would not recommend. And it's pretty expensive

This place had been abdolutely ridiculous.  We had heard from a friend that this was a great place for pizza in DC, but boy were we disappointed.  We looked at thier online menu, and decided what we wanted - steak and alfredo pizza and a pasta.  We call and tell them the address for delivery, they say fine.  They said they wouldnt sub out steak for chicken alferdo pizza.  Ok fine.  We regroup, call back, and they say it will be 57.50 for pasta and a medium pizza.  What the heck!?  I am so hungry at this point I say fine... Then they call back and tell me they don't deliver here.  I'm done.  Never again.
Great pizza!

Horrible experience. Ordered delivery. Girl over the phone was completely rude. Had to repeat my order a few times. After ordering she hung up the phone on me. I called back to ask about how the food would be delivered to the hotel room and she rudely said "ma'am your food isn't even ready". Yeah I know...just placed order. So rude!!!!

I order from Pizzolis once a week.  Have never had a bad experience with the food.  I usually order thin crust Hunger Buster pizza and wings.  Not a sit down place unless you use the picnic table outside.  Much more of a neighborhood take out / delivery place.  A little bit higher than ordering from Dominos or Papa Johns, but then again you get a much better product I believe.  I order online and within 15 minutes it's ready - very quick and good.  Pizza sauce is mild but flavorful.  They offer other things as well beyond pizza; appetizers, sandwiches, salads, a few deserts and drinks.  Again, not really a sit down place however.
Extremely late. Asked for tip in advance. Terrible customer service. Don't order with them
Good for the area. DC pizza isn't great overall but this is passable.

What a terrible terrible shame. I have ordered here frequently and at least 50 percent of the time, the order is wrong. Today I ordered a large extra cheese and they gave me a large with mushrooms. This happens so frequently! They are never apologetic but just say, "ok it'll be 20 mins." How can this business get by on faulty orders and a bad attitude? I am done w this place. What a shame. Get better pizza done CORRECTLY with a much better attitude somewhere else.
Avoid this place! Expensive as hell, and truly awful. I had a "cheese calzone" and it literally was just the bread and cheese. For $12!!! Go to wiseguys!

Can I give negative stars? not likely so I guess ill have to settle for giving one...  let me start at the beginning. I ordered an extra large one topping pepperoni pizza. simple, right? Well it was delivered to my apartment with 2 fingernails in it. when I called to complain I was told there is no way. They offered to give me a credit for my pizza and keep it on my account. i cooled down, and thought.. okay, they had a bad night. i decide to order from them again, and ask to talk to the manager to bring up the credit that was "on file" this credit was nowhere to be found. after asking him how this could have happened, he told me in the future, you need to remember the manager on duty's name.  Once I got past their bad book keeping, I was rudely told he had other customers to attend to.  Gani (manger I was speaking to) hung up on me mid sentence.

The things that I specifically asked to be taken off the salad were still on. The salad was large and only came with one small packet of dressing. The "JUMBO" wings were too salty and over-cooked. Good pizza.  By the slice took a while.

Pizza was good, however check your bag before you leave. I specifically asked if there were plates, utensils and salad dressing in the bag.  I was told there was.  Got home, not there.  Very aggravating.

Great neighborhood joint with personality and pretty good pizza. Wings were average to a bit above average but very wet (just not the way I prefer them).  Salads looked excellent. Quick service. The sidewalk seating was a great way to catch the flavor of the neighborhood.

moved to the neighborhood recently, and closest pizza joint. went there several times, as the owner was nice and would always rave about how the ingredients were fresh and the pizza was the best we would find. quickly realized it was just not very good. went in tonight for a jumbo cheese slice of pizza. cashier was hitting on a drunk girl as i walked in, and took probably ~15 seconds to acknowledge me. put the order in, and he went back to hitting on her (i was the only other person inside). she walked out once she got her pizza, and he commented to me on how he "had no chance" with her. flash forward to the ~7 minutes to me getting my pizza. walk back to my house, open it, and see half the crust is ripped off (picture uploaded on yelp). i call them, and am immediately put on hold (understandable, late night). when he picks up, i tell him that half my crust is ripped off and he asks if i want to order another slice. i tell him again, and after a failure to communicate i hang up in defeat and give up. they call back, and he asks me if i had a problem with the slice (I'm a little impressed with that). i tell him i am coming over, and walk back to the pizzolis. they already have another slice ready for me, and he half asses apologized for the mistake and seemed annoyed that i came back and was taking up his time. they blame it on the pizza getting caught in the oven, but you be the judge (picture uploaded on yelp). as soon as i had my hand on the box he went back to talking to his friends in the store. i threw out their replacement slice (for fear of "waiting" type things on the slice) and ordered papa johns.

Man oh man is this place good!  My new favorite NY style pizza outside of Manhattan.  It's an unassuming little joint but there were few food options close to the Cambria hotel we stayed at on 9th and O.  It was a quick walk over to 12th.  Coming around the corner I smelled this incredible smell, and it wound up being Pizzoli's.  It's small on the inside but they have a patio and amazing food.  They also have a large drink selection, cakes, and a full case of Ben and Jerry's.  We had a vegetarian version of their spinach pie and it was crazy good.  The pie was a little small for what we normally get as a medium, but it was piled up with sun dried tomatoes, carmelized onions and spinach, I ate 6 slices.  Crazy good pizza.  When we are back in DC we are eating here.
Good, cheap pizza.

I just stopped by this place (April 8, 2014 around 930pm). I called ahead to see if they sold by the slice. When I came in I asked what type of slice I would get (new york, chicago, other) and the girl could not tell me. Worse, she didnt care and only proceeded to point and a black and white photocopy (small) pasted on the wall. I still ordered a slice with ham and they gave me a slice with ham just thrown on top of it at the last minute. To be quiet honest i walked away and threw most of it on the garbage.
They are so delish! Fast, Friendly, and let me just say the yummiest all around! Everything I've tried is fresh and incredible!

Pizzoli's is typically my go-to place for delivery. The sause is a good mix of spicy/sweet and the ingredients taste good as well. I like the hand-tossed crust for a slightly thicker pizza-- it's not as thick as Pizza Hut or Papa John's hand-tossed and that's just fine with me.  My only reservation is that the delivery can take a while and they've forgotten a drink a time or two. They've only made mistakes like that when it's basically right before they close so I try cut them a little slack. I think twice before ordering late or if I'm in hurry--- but I do think twice because it's pretty good.
Some of the best pizza I've ever had to go along with an extremely helpful and friendly service. Will def be coming back. Recommended to everyone.
One of my best to eat in the weekend!
Excellent place for a quick bite to eat. I have never had an issue. Might be pricy for some people.
